{"video_id": "UvVVMAJ0Wgc", "title": "SB 1.18.49-50 | HH Stoka Krishna Swami | 01-05-2023 | Daily Evening Bhagavatam Discourse", "speaker": "HH Stoka Krishna Swami", "youtube_url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UvVVMAJ0Wgc", "duration": 971, "segments": [{"start": 0.0, "end": 8.2, "text": " Om Agyanati Mirandhasya Gyananjanishalakaya Chaksharunmilitam Yena Tasmai Shri Gurave Namaha"}, {"start": 8.2, "end": 16.12, "text": " Namah Om Vishnupadaya Krishna Preshthaya Bhutale Shri Mate Bhaktivedanta Swamin Nithinamine"}, {"start": 16.12, "end": 24.32, "text": " Namaste Saraswate Deve Gauravani Pracharine Nirvishesha Shunyavadi Pashchatya Deshatarine"}, {"start": 24.32, "end": 32.4, "text": " Jaya Shri Krishna Chaitanya Prabhu Nithyananda Shri Advaita Gadadhara Shiva Sadhi Gauravakta Vrinda"}, {"start": 32.4, "end": 39.620000000000005, "text": " Hare Krishna Hare Krishna Krishna Krishna Hare Hare Hare Rama Hare Rama Rama Rama Hare Hare"}, {"start": 39.620000000000005, "end": 45.46, "text": " Om Namo Bhagavate Vasudevaya Narayanam Namaskritya Naram Chai Vanarottamam"}, {"start": 45.46, "end": 49.44, "text": " Deveem Saraswateem Vyasam Tato Jayam Udi Rayet"}, {"start": 49.44, "end": 54.3, "text": " In this session we will be discussing from two verses, the 49th and the 58th."}, {"start": 54.32, "end": 58.6, "text": " verses of the 18th chapter of the first canto of Srimad Bhagavatam."}, {"start": 58.96, "end": 60.980000000000004, "text": " These are the last two verses of this chapter."}, {"start": 61.32, "end": 64.68, "text": " This chapter is entitled Maharaj Parikshit Cursed by a Brahmana Boy."}, {"start": 65.82, "end": 77.1, "text": " The 49th verse, Iti Putra Krita Ghena Sonu Tapto Mahamunihi Swayam Viprakrto Ragna Naiva"}, {"start": 77.1, "end": 79.68, "text": " Agham Tad Achintayat."}, {"start": 81.3, "end": 82.88, "text": " The translation is,"}, {"start": 83.74000000000001, "end": 84.3, "text": " The Sage Dharamuddin,"}, {"start": 84.32000000000001, "end": 87.28, "text": " thus regretted the sin committed by his own son."}, {"start": 88.04, "end": 92.10000000000001, "text": " He did not take the insult paid by the king very seriously."}, {"start": 94.10000000000001, "end": 98.42, "text": " Now this is summarizing the incident itself entirely."}, {"start": 99.42, "end": 101.76, "text": " The whole chapter which is describing this incident,"}, {"start": 102.30000000000001, "end": 105.22000000000001, "text": " leading to Parikshit Maharaj renouncing his kingdom"}, {"start": 105.22000000000001, "end": 110.26, "text": " and thereby meeting Shikadeva Goswami and Bhagavatam being spoken"}, {"start": 110.26, "end": 114.18, "text": " and revealed for the benefit of the whole world."}, {"start": 114.32000000000001, "end": 117.10000000000001, "text": " So in the Purport Shila, Prabhupada says,"}, {"start": 117.64000000000001, "end": 120.2, "text": " The whole incident is now cleared up."}, {"start": 121.26, "end": 122.30000000000001, "text": " How is it cleared up?"}, {"start": 122.86000000000001, "end": 126.24000000000001, "text": " Maharaj Parikshit's garlanding the sage with a dead snake"}, {"start": 126.24000000000001, "end": 128.66, "text": " was not at all a very serious offense."}, {"start": 130.46, "end": 134.8, "text": " But Shringi's cursing the king was a serious offense."}, {"start": 136.34, "end": 137.60000000000002, "text": " So it's very clear."}, {"start": 137.60000000000002, "end": 140.14000000000001, "text": " Now, Parikshit's action,"}, {"start": 142.10000000000002, "end": 143.34, "text": " which was the,"}, {"start": 143.34, "end": 149.12, "text": " which led to the whole incident of cursing by the"}, {"start": 149.12, "end": 152.12, "text": " Shamika Rishi's son,"}, {"start": 152.12, "end": 155.12, "text": " it is not at all a serious offense."}, {"start": 155.12, "end": 163.12, "text": " And the cursing by Shringi was a very, very serious offense."}, {"start": 163.12, "end": 167.12, "text": " Now, how is it adjusted?"}, {"start": 167.12, "end": 169.12, "text": " Very nicely it's adjusted."}, {"start": 169.12, "end": 173.12, "text": " The serious offense is committed by foolish child only."}, {"start": 173.34, "end": 177.34, "text": " Therefore, he deserved to be pardoned by the Supreme Lord."}, {"start": 177.34, "end": 189.34, "text": " Because the curse was given by a foolish boy."}, {"start": 190.16, "end": 193.52, "text": " And the small boy has made a mistake unknowingly,"}, {"start": 194.52, "end": 197.2, "text": " immaturely, foolishly he has done a mistake."}, {"start": 197.2, "end": 200.52, "text": " So he deserved to be pardoned by the Supreme Lord."}, {"start": 201.28, "end": 203.32, "text": " Although it was not,"}, {"start": 203.34, "end": 205.34, "text": " it was not possible to get free from the sinful reaction."}, {"start": 205.34, "end": 207.34, "text": " The reaction is,"}, {"start": 207.34, "end": 211.34, "text": " the sinful activity is very, very, very serious."}, {"start": 211.34, "end": 220.34, "text": " So ordinarily a person cannot get away by committing such a very, very serious sinful activity."}, {"start": 220.34, "end": 222.34, "text": " A grave sinful activity."}, {"start": 222.34, "end": 224.34, "text": " Nobody can get away."}, {"start": 224.34, "end": 228.34, "text": " But this case, specific case,"}, {"start": 228.34, "end": 232.34, "text": " the foolish boy deserves to be pardoned."}, {"start": 233.34, "end": 241.34, "text": " Now, Maharaj Pariksit also did not mind the curse offered to him by a foolish Brahmana."}, {"start": 241.34, "end": 247.34, "text": " This is Maharaj Pariksit's personal reaction."}, {"start": 247.34, "end": 251.34, "text": " When he heard that he is going to die within seven days."}, {"start": 251.34, "end": 257.34000000000003, "text": " Being, having been cursed by the son of Shamika Rishi."}, {"start": 257.34000000000003, "end": 259.34000000000003, "text": " So he did not mind at all."}, {"start": 259.34000000000003, "end": 261.34000000000003, "text": " On the contrary,"}, {"start": 261.34000000000003, "end": 267.34000000000003, "text": " he took full advantage of the awkward situation."}, {"start": 267.34000000000003, "end": 272.34000000000003, "text": " This clumsy situation in which Pariksit Maharaj had been placed."}, {"start": 272.34000000000003, "end": 273.34000000000003, "text": " He took full advantage."}, {"start": 273.34000000000003, "end": 274.34000000000003, "text": " What did he do?"}, {"start": 274.34000000000003, "end": 276.34000000000003, "text": " By a great will of the Lord,"}, {"start": 276.34000000000003, "end": 279.34000000000003, "text": " Maharaj Pariksit achieved the highest perfection of life"}, {"start": 279.34000000000003, "end": 282.34000000000003, "text": " through the grace of Srila Shukadeva Goswami."}, {"start": 282.34000000000003, "end": 287.34000000000003, "text": " The events that led to"}, {"start": 287.34000000000003, "end": 294.34000000000003, "text": " Pariksit Maharaj achieving the highest perfection of life."}, {"start": 294.34000000000003, "end": 299.34000000000003, "text": " The curse was in no way an impediment for him to achieve the highest perfection."}, {"start": 299.34000000000003, "end": 306.34000000000003, "text": " Rather it became a kind of boon in disguise."}, {"start": 306.34000000000003, "end": 308.34000000000003, "text": " They say boon in disguise."}, {"start": 308.34000000000003, "end": 315.34000000000003, "text": " So it came as something very, very beneficial for Pariksit."}, {"start": 315.34000000000003, "end": 320.34000000000003, "text": " That he took advantage by renouncing his kingdom"}, {"start": 320.34000000000003, "end": 325.34000000000003, "text": " and trying to prepare for meeting with death within one week."}, {"start": 325.34000000000003, "end": 327.34000000000003, "text": " And in the course of that,"}, {"start": 327.34000000000003, "end": 330.34000000000003, "text": " he happened to meet Shukadeva Goswami and"}, {"start": 330.34000000000003, "end": 334.34000000000003, "text": " Shukadeva Goswami spoke the entire Bhagavatam to Pariksit Maharaj."}, {"start": 334.34000000000003, "end": 337.34000000000003, "text": " Pariksit Maharaj got enlightened and thereby"}, {"start": 337.34000000000003, "end": 341.34000000000003, "text": " he achieved the ultimate liberation and"}, {"start": 341.34000000000003, "end": 344.34000000000003, "text": " also others who heard also achieved the same destination."}, {"start": 344.34000000000003, "end": 347.34000000000003, "text": " And in future,"}, {"start": 347.34000000000003, "end": 350.34000000000003, "text": " anybody by hearing Bhagavatam"}, {"start": 350.34000000000003, "end": 353.34000000000003, "text": " can get the highest perfection of life simply by hearing"}, {"start": 353.34000000000003, "end": 356.34000000000003, "text": " like Pariksit Maharaj did."}, {"start": 356.34000000000003, "end": 359.34000000000003, "text": " Simply hearing Bhagavatam."}, {"start": 359.34000000000003, "end": 362.34000000000003, "text": " Actually it was a desire of the Lord."}, {"start": 362.34000000000003, "end": 366.34000000000003, "text": " The whole series of events was a desire of the Lord."}, {"start": 366.34000000000003, "end": 370.34000000000003, "text": " And Maharaj Pariksit, Rishi Shamika"}, {"start": 370.34000000000003, "end": 373.34000000000003, "text": " and Rishi Shamika's son Shringi"}, {"start": 373.34000000000003, "end": 376.34000000000003, "text": " were all instrumental"}, {"start": 376.34000000000003, "end": 379.34000000000003, "text": " in fulfilling the desire of the Lord."}, {"start": 379.34000000000003, "end": 382.34000000000003, "text": " The Lord wants to do something in the material world."}, {"start": 382.34000000000003, "end": 384.34000000000003, "text": " Sometimes he directly does it."}, {"start": 384.34000000000003, "end": 387.34000000000003, "text": " Sometimes he indirectly does it through somebody."}, {"start": 387.34000000000003, "end": 390.34000000000003, "text": " Through some instruments."}, {"start": 390.34000000000003, "end": 393.34000000000003, "text": " Like it is actually Krishna only who killed"}, {"start": 393.34000000000003, "end": 396.34000000000003, "text": " all those Kauravas"}, {"start": 396.34000000000003, "end": 399.34000000000003, "text": " on the battlefield of Kurukshetra."}, {"start": 399.34000000000003, "end": 402.34000000000003, "text": " But Krishna did it through"}, {"start": 403.34000000000003, "end": 409.34000000000003, "text": " the Pandavas headed by Arjuna."}, {"start": 409.34000000000003, "end": 411.34000000000003, "text": " So Krishna tells Arjuna"}, {"start": 411.34000000000003, "end": 416.34000000000003, "text": " that I have already killed all these Kauravas."}, {"start": 416.34000000000003, "end": 419.34000000000003, "text": " You can only be an instrument."}, {"start": 419.34000000000003, "end": 424.34000000000003, "text": " As Kala, Krishna is always acting in this material world."}, {"start": 424.34000000000003, "end": 427.34000000000003, "text": " Kala destroys everything in course of time."}, {"start": 427.34000000000003, "end": 431.34000000000003, "text": " So destruction by Kala nobody can avoid."}, {"start": 431.34000000000003, "end": 440.34000000000003, "text": " But sometimes Kala also uses some instrument"}, {"start": 440.34000000000003, "end": 443.34000000000003, "text": " to kill somebody."}, {"start": 443.34000000000003, "end": 446.34000000000003, "text": " It is like people say natural death"}, {"start": 446.34000000000003, "end": 451.34000000000003, "text": " and death by some vehicle accident."}, {"start": 451.34000000000003, "end": 453.34000000000003, "text": " So when it is death by vehicle accident"}, {"start": 453.34000000000003, "end": 456.34000000000003, "text": " people think oh he died because of vehicle accident."}, {"start": 456.34000000000003, "end": 461.34000000000003, "text": " No it is Kala only who is using the vehicle accident"}, {"start": 461.34000000000003, "end": 464.34000000000003, "text": " as an instrument"}, {"start": 464.34000000000003, "end": 469.34000000000003, "text": " to actually destroy."}, {"start": 469.34000000000003, "end": 472.34000000000003, "text": " Even if somebody dies a natural death"}, {"start": 472.34000000000003, "end": 474.34000000000003, "text": " it is Kala only"}, {"start": 474.34000000000003, "end": 477.34000000000003, "text": " who is actually bringing about the destruction."}, {"start": 477.34000000000003, "end": 479.34000000000003, "text": " So similarly"}, {"start": 479.34000000000003, "end": 482.34000000000003, "text": " the Lord is using"}, {"start": 482.34000000000003, "end": 485.34000000000003, "text": " Maharaj Pariksit, Rishi Shamika"}, {"start": 485.34000000000003, "end": 487.34000000000003, "text": " and Shamika Sanshungi"}, {"start": 487.34000000000003, "end": 489.34000000000003, "text": " as instruments for his purpose."}, {"start": 489.34000000000003, "end": 490.34000000000003, "text": " That"}, {"start": 490.34000000000003, "end": 495.34000000000003, "text": " the Srimad Bhagavatam be spoken."}, {"start": 495.34000000000003, "end": 497.34000000000003, "text": " None of them were put into difficulty"}, {"start": 497.34000000000003, "end": 499.34000000000003, "text": " because everything was done"}, {"start": 499.34000000000003, "end": 503.34000000000003, "text": " in relation with the Supreme Person."}, {"start": 503.34000000000003, "end": 506.34000000000003, "text": " So when everything is in relationship with Krishna"}, {"start": 506.34000000000003, "end": 507.34000000000003, "text": " nothing is bad,"}, {"start": 507.34000000000003, "end": 508.34000000000003, "text": " nothing is wrong,"}, {"start": 508.34000000000003, "end": 516.34, "text": " nothing is punishable."}, {"start": 516.34, "end": 517.34, "text": " The 50th verse,"}, {"start": 517.34, "end": 519.34, "text": " the last verse of this chapter."}, {"start": 519.34, "end": 521.34, "text": " prayashaha sadavo loke"}, {"start": 521.34, "end": 524.34, "text": " paraidhvanveshu yojitah"}, {"start": 524.34, "end": 527.34, "text": " na vyathanti na hrishyanti"}, {"start": 527.34, "end": 532.34, "text": " yata atma agunashrayah"}, {"start": 532.34, "end": 533.34, "text": " The meaning of this verse is"}, {"start": 533.34, "end": 536.34, "text": " generally the transcendentalists"}, {"start": 536.34, "end": 538.34, "text": " even though engaged by others"}, {"start": 538.34, "end": 540.34, "text": " in the dualities of the material world"}, {"start": 540.34, "end": 543.34, "text": " are not distressed."}, {"start": 543.34, "end": 545.34, "text": " Nor do they take pleasure"}, {"start": 545.34, "end": 546.34, "text": " in worldly things"}, {"start": 546.34, "end": 547.34, "text": " for"}, {"start": 547.34, "end": 548.34, "text": " they are"}, {"start": 548.34, "end": 552.34, "text": " transcendentally engaged."}, {"start": 552.34, "end": 555.34, "text": " Prabhupada explains this very nicely"}, {"start": 555.34, "end": 557.34, "text": " that"}, {"start": 557.34, "end": 560.34, "text": " those who are transcendentalists"}, {"start": 560.34, "end": 562.34, "text": " they are described as"}, {"start": 562.34, "end": 566.34, "text": " here"}, {"start": 566.34, "end": 569.34, "text": " sadavaha"}, {"start": 569.34, "end": 574.34, "text": " transcendentalists, saintly persons."}, {"start": 574.34, "end": 576.34, "text": " They are never distressed"}, {"start": 576.34, "end": 578.34, "text": " or they are never"}, {"start": 578.34, "end": 579.34, "text": " happy"}, {"start": 579.34, "end": 581.34, "text": " in this material world."}, {"start": 581.34, "end": 582.34, "text": " Why?"}, {"start": 582.34, "end": 586.34, "text": " Because they are always spiritually engaged."}, {"start": 588.34, "end": 590.34, "text": " So they don't"}, {"start": 590.34, "end": 592.34, "text": " even consider"}, {"start": 592.34, "end": 595.34, "text": " what is the material situation."}, {"start": 596.34, "end": 597.34, "text": " As materialists"}, {"start": 597.34, "end": 599.34, "text": " or as people who are"}, {"start": 600.34, "end": 602.34, "text": " under the"}, {"start": 603.34, "end": 605.34, "text": " crutches of maya"}, {"start": 605.34, "end": 607.34, "text": " we are always concerned"}, {"start": 607.34, "end": 611.34, "text": " whether we are getting material pleasure"}, {"start": 611.34, "end": 613.34, "text": " or material happiness"}, {"start": 613.34, "end": 616.34, "text": " and we try to avoid material distress."}, {"start": 616.34, "end": 619.34, "text": " We are busy always."}, {"start": 619.34, "end": 622.34, "text": " Conditioned souls are always busy"}, {"start": 622.34, "end": 624.34, "text": " trying to avoid material distress"}, {"start": 624.34, "end": 627.34, "text": " and trying to maximize material happiness."}, {"start": 627.34, "end": 629.34, "text": " But the transcendentalists,"}, {"start": 629.34, "end": 631.34, "text": " the spiritualists"}, {"start": 631.34, "end": 633.34, "text": " those who are seriously engaged"}, {"start": 633.34, "end": 636.34, "text": " always in spiritual activities"}, {"start": 636.34, "end": 638.34, "text": " they never care"}, {"start": 638.34, "end": 640.34, "text": " whether"}, {"start": 640.34, "end": 642.34, "text": " by some"}, {"start": 642.34, "end": 643.34, "text": " reason"}, {"start": 643.34, "end": 645.34, "text": " they get material happiness"}, {"start": 645.34, "end": 646.34, "text": " or material distress."}, {"start": 646.34, "end": 648.34, "text": " They don't care for either."}, {"start": 649.34, "end": 651.34, "text": " So Srila Prabhupada explains in the purport"}, {"start": 651.34, "end": 653.34, "text": " the transcendentalists"}, {"start": 653.34, "end": 654.34, "text": " are of"}, {"start": 655.34, "end": 657.34, "text": " three kinds."}, {"start": 658.34, "end": 660.34, "text": " The emperic philosophers"}, {"start": 660.34, "end": 661.34, "text": " the mystics"}, {"start": 661.34, "end": 663.34, "text": " and the devotees of the Lord."}, {"start": 663.34, "end": 668.34, "text": " The jnanis, yogis and bhaktas."}, {"start": 668.34, "end": 670.34, "text": " There is a samskara for that."}, {"start": 670.34, "end": 672.34, "text": " Empiric philosophers"}, {"start": 672.34, "end": 674.34, "text": " aim at the perfection of merging"}, {"start": 674.34, "end": 676.34, "text": " into the being of the absolute."}, {"start": 676.34, "end": 678.34, "text": " What is the ultimate goal"}, {"start": 678.34, "end": 681.34, "text": " of the emperic philosophers"}, {"start": 681.34, "end": 682.34, "text": " the jnanis"}, {"start": 682.34, "end": 684.34, "text": " those who cultivate spiritual knowledge"}, {"start": 684.34, "end": 686.34, "text": " with the aim of"}, {"start": 686.34, "end": 688.34, "text": " merging into the"}, {"start": 688.34, "end": 690.34, "text": " absolute truth."}, {"start": 690.34, "end": 694.34, "text": " Sayujya mukti"}, {"start": 694.34, "end": 696.34, "text": " they want sayujya mukti."}, {"start": 698.34, "end": 700.34, "text": " Mystics aim at perceiving"}, {"start": 700.34, "end": 702.34, "text": " the all pervading super soul."}, {"start": 702.34, "end": 704.34, "text": " Mystics are"}, {"start": 704.34, "end": 706.34, "text": " the ashtanga yogis."}, {"start": 706.34, "end": 708.34, "text": " Their goal"}, {"start": 708.34, "end": 710.34, "text": " is to"}, {"start": 710.34, "end": 712.34, "text": " realize"}, {"start": 712.34, "end": 714.34, "text": " the Paramatma"}, {"start": 714.34, "end": 716.34, "text": " who is all pervading in this material world."}, {"start": 716.34, "end": 717.34, "text": " He is"}, {"start": 717.34, "end": 719.34, "text": " Paramatma is present in everyone's heart"}, {"start": 719.34, "end": 721.34, "text": " of every living being's heart"}, {"start": 721.34, "end": 723.34, "text": " and Paramatma is also present"}, {"start": 723.34, "end": 725.34, "text": " entered into every atom."}, {"start": 725.34, "end": 727.34, "text": " So they want to perceive that Paramatma."}, {"start": 727.34, "end": 729.34, "text": " This is their perfection."}, {"start": 729.34, "end": 731.34, "text": " The ashtanga yogis."}, {"start": 733.34, "end": 734.34, "text": " And devotees of the Lord"}, {"start": 734.34, "end": 736.34, "text": " are engaged in the transcendental loving service"}, {"start": 736.34, "end": 738.34, "text": " of the personality of God."}, {"start": 738.34, "end": 739.34, "text": " Devotees"}, {"start": 739.34, "end": 740.34, "text": " pure devotees"}, {"start": 740.34, "end": 741.34, "text": " bhaktas"}, {"start": 741.34, "end": 743.34, "text": " they only want one thing."}, {"start": 744.34, "end": 746.34, "text": " They want"}, {"start": 746.34, "end": 748.34, "text": " to be always engaged"}, {"start": 748.34, "end": 751.34, "text": " in the transcendental loving service of Krishna."}, {"start": 753.34, "end": 755.34, "text": " Now Srila Prabhupada further explains"}, {"start": 759.34, "end": 761.34, "text": " Since Brahman, Paramatma and Bhagavan"}, {"start": 761.34, "end": 763.34, "text": " are different phases of the same transcendence"}, {"start": 763.34, "end": 765.34, "text": " This is explained in the Bhagavatam."}, {"start": 765.34, "end": 767.34, "text": " vadantita tattva vidas tattvam yad"}, {"start": 767.34, "end": 769.34, "text": " jnanam advayam"}, {"start": 769.34, "end": 771.34, "text": " brahmeti paramatmeti bhavaneti"}, {"start": 771.34, "end": 773.34, "text": " sabhyate"}, {"start": 773.34, "end": 775.34, "text": " All categories of transcendentalists"}, {"start": 775.34, "end": 777.34, "text": " their aim is"}, {"start": 777.34, "end": 779.34, "text": " the absolute truth only."}, {"start": 779.34, "end": 781.34, "text": " But there are three features"}, {"start": 781.34, "end": 782.34, "text": " of the absolute truth"}, {"start": 782.34, "end": 784.34, "text": " and accordingly"}, {"start": 784.34, "end": 786.34, "text": " the three categories of transcendentalists"}, {"start": 786.34, "end": 788.34, "text": " are aiming for one of the features."}, {"start": 789.34, "end": 791.34, "text": " The jnanis aim for Brahman"}, {"start": 792.34, "end": 794.34, "text": " The mystic yogis or the ashtanga yogis"}, {"start": 794.34, "end": 796.34, "text": " aim for Paramatma"}, {"start": 797.34, "end": 799.34, "text": " and the devotees"}, {"start": 799.34, "end": 801.34, "text": " or bhaktas"}, {"start": 801.34, "end": 803.34, "text": " bhakti yogis"}, {"start": 803.34, "end": 805.34, "text": " aim at Bhagavan."}, {"start": 807.34, "end": 809.34, "text": " But Brahman, Paramatma and Bhagavan"}, {"start": 809.34, "end": 812.34, "text": " are described in the Bhagavatam"}, {"start": 812.34, "end": 814.34, "text": " as advayagyana"}, {"start": 814.34, "end": 816.34, "text": " non-dual substance"}, {"start": 816.34, "end": 818.34, "text": " of the absolute truth."}, {"start": 818.34, "end": 820.34, "text": " They are all the same."}, {"start": 822.34, "end": 824.34, "text": " Therefore"}, {"start": 824.34, "end": 825.34, "text": " Prabhupada says"}, {"start": 825.34, "end": 827.34, "text": " these three categories of transcendentalists"}, {"start": 827.34, "end": 830.34, "text": " are beyond the three modes of material nature."}, {"start": 830.34, "end": 833.34, "text": " All of them are transcendental to the three modes."}, {"start": 833.34, "end": 835.34, "text": " Agunashrayaha"}, {"start": 835.34, "end": 837.34, "text": " Atma"}, {"start": 837.34, "end": 839.34, "text": " Agunashraya"}, {"start": 839.34, "end": 841.34, "text": " Those are transcendentalists."}, {"start": 841.34, "end": 843.34, "text": " They are always beyond the modes."}, {"start": 844.34, "end": 846.34, "text": " Material distress and happiness"}, {"start": 846.34, "end": 848.34, "text": " are products of the three modes."}, {"start": 849.34, "end": 850.34, "text": " Always"}, {"start": 850.34, "end": 852.34, "text": " interactions of the three gunas"}, {"start": 852.34, "end": 854.34, "text": " produces either"}, {"start": 854.34, "end": 856.34, "text": " distress or happiness."}, {"start": 856.34, "end": 858.34, "text": " Material distress or material happiness."}, {"start": 858.34, "end": 860.34, "text": " That's the nature of this material existence."}, {"start": 861.34, "end": 863.34, "text": " Therefore the causes"}, {"start": 863.34, "end": 865.34, "text": " of such material distress and happiness"}, {"start": 865.34, "end": 868.34, "text": " have nothing to do with the transcendentalists."}, {"start": 869.34, "end": 871.34, "text": " Transcendentalists are engaged in"}, {"start": 871.34, "end": 874.34, "text": " spiritual activities"}, {"start": 874.34, "end": 876.34, "text": " because of which"}, {"start": 876.34, "end": 878.34, "text": " they don't care"}, {"start": 878.34, "end": 880.34, "text": " whether a material situation"}, {"start": 880.34, "end": 882.34, "text": " gives them happiness or distress."}, {"start": 882.34, "end": 884.34, "text": " They don't care for that."}, {"start": 884.34, "end": 886.34, "text": " Because they don't want"}, {"start": 886.34, "end": 888.34, "text": " they neither want happiness nor want distress."}, {"start": 888.34, "end": 889.34, "text": " What do they want?"}, {"start": 889.34, "end": 891.34, "text": " They want the supreme."}, {"start": 891.34, "end": 893.34, "text": " They only want the supreme."}, {"start": 893.34, "end": 894.34, "text": " The king was a devotee"}, {"start": 894.34, "end": 896.34, "text": " and the rishi was a mystic."}, {"start": 896.34, "end": 898.34, "text": " That's why all this is explained."}, {"start": 898.34, "end": 900.34, "text": " Parikshit Maharaj"}, {"start": 900.34, "end": 902.34, "text": " was"}, {"start": 902.34, "end": 904.34, "text": " a pure devotee of the supreme lord."}, {"start": 904.34, "end": 906.34, "text": " He was a"}, {"start": 906.34, "end": 908.34, "text": " he was a bhakta."}, {"start": 910.34, "end": 912.34, "text": " And"}, {"start": 912.34, "end": 914.34, "text": " Shamika Rishi"}, {"start": 914.34, "end": 916.34, "text": " was"}, {"start": 916.34, "end": 918.34, "text": " a mystic yogi."}, {"start": 918.34, "end": 920.34, "text": " So he was"}, {"start": 920.34, "end": 922.34, "text": " Shamika Rishi"}, {"start": 922.34, "end": 924.34, "text": " was also a transcendentalist"}, {"start": 924.34, "end": 926.34, "text": " seriously engaged in"}, {"start": 926.34, "end": 927.34, "text": " Ashtanga Yoga practice."}, {"start": 927.34, "end": 929.34, "text": " That's why he was sitting in trance"}, {"start": 929.34, "end": 930.34, "text": " trying to"}, {"start": 930.34, "end": 932.34, "text": " fix his attention on the"}, {"start": 932.34, "end": 934.34, "text": " Paramatma within the heart."}, {"start": 934.34, "end": 936.34, "text": " So therefore"}, {"start": 936.34, "end": 938.34, "text": " both of them were unattached"}, {"start": 938.34, "end": 940.34, "text": " to the accidental incident"}, {"start": 940.34, "end": 942.34, "text": " created by the supreme lord."}, {"start": 942.34, "end": 944.34, "text": " Parikshit Maharaj did not mind"}, {"start": 944.34, "end": 946.34, "text": " the cursing"}, {"start": 946.34, "end": 947.34, "text": " of that boy."}, {"start": 947.34, "end": 949.34, "text": " Shamika Rishi did not mind"}, {"start": 949.34, "end": 951.34, "text": " Parikshit Maharaj insulting him."}, {"start": 951.34, "end": 953.34, "text": " Both are transcendentalists."}, {"start": 953.34, "end": 955.34, "text": " The playful child"}, {"start": 955.34, "end": 957.34, "text": " was an instrument in"}, {"start": 957.34, "end": 959.34, "text": " fulfilling the lord's will."}, {"start": 959.34, "end": 961.34, "text": " Other than these two"}, {"start": 961.34, "end": 963.34, "text": " the child was simply"}, {"start": 963.34, "end": 965.34, "text": " an instrument in the"}, {"start": 965.34, "end": 967.34, "text": " lord's plan."}, {"start": 967.34, "end": 969.34, "text": " So I will stop here."}, {"start": 969.34, "end": 971.34, "text": " Thank you very much. Hare Krishna."}]}